# Autonomous loop — forbidden terminal commands

When running `/next-task` or any autonomous TASKS.md loop work:

**Never run** (halt with `[?]` if the task truly requires one — do not bypass):

- `git push --force` / `git push -f`
- `git commit --amend`
- `git commit --no-verify` / `git commit --no-gpg-sign`
- `git add -A` / `git add .` / `git add --all`
- `rm -rf` or broad `rm` on project paths
- `git reset --hard`, `git clean -fd`, destructive `git checkout --`

**Prefer** explicit-path `git add <path>` only, per task `Outputs:` and the pre-commit allow-list.

Project deny rules also live in `.cursor/cli.json` (`permissions.deny`). Cursor IDE has no separate terminal deny-list UI — use allowlist mode plus these denies and **Settings → Cursor Settings → Agents → Protection** (File-Deletion Protection on).
